Privacy Policy for Shake2Light

Last Updated: September 17, 2025

1. General Information
The Shake2Light application ("app", "we", "our") is designed as a tool to turn your device's flashlight on and off by shaking. This privacy policy informs you about our policies regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of information when you use our application.

Important: Our application does not collect, store, or transmit any personal user data. All data processing occurs locally on your device.

2. Permissions Used by the Application
Our application requests the following permissions:

CAMERA Permission - Required to access the camera flash, which is used as a flashlight. We do not access the camera or any images/video.

FOREGROUND_SERVICE Permission - Required for the background service operation that tracks device movements to activate the flashlight by shaking.

3. Information Collection and Use
Our application DOES NOT COLLECT and DOES NOT TRANSMIT any data:

We do not collect personal information

We do not request access to contacts, location, or media files

We do not track user activities

We do not use analytics tools or cookies

The application has no internet access and does not transmit data

All data processing (processing accelerometer signals to detect shaking) occurs exclusively on your device without any external transmission.

4. Device Sensors
The application uses the following sensors on your device:

Accelerometer - To detect the shaking gesture

Proximity sensor (if available) - To determine if the device is in a pocket to prevent accidental activation

Data from these sensors is processed exclusively locally and immediately removed from memory after processing.

5. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.
